{
  "stem": "10446.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In other words, you had to pay a substantial part of your fortune, I think it was 60%, to the Nazi party or to the Reich in order to get permission to leave Germany.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They called it Reich Flight Tax, which was ironic because this was a forced exodus.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Now, our money was tied up in the brewery, in real estate and the, and the brewery.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So until the brewery was sold or unless the brewery was sold, there was no way for us to pay that tax.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because the tax was of a very high percentage, and our money, as I said, was tied up in that business.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So we found it impossible to get our passports and to get our visas and leave the country [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] until the, until Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But one thing I have to mention.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Through an inextricable error of the German authorities, my father and I got our passports back.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They took the passports away, must have been in 1938.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in-- about six months later, we got our-- my father and I, not my mother and Hella, got our passports back, which was an out-and-out error, because you did not get your passport until the, that tax was paid, which we couldn't.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The minute we got our passports, we-- my father went to the Swiss consulate and got himself a Swiss transit visa, and I went to the French consulate and got a French transit visa, which I was able to get because we had business connections because of our hops business with France.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Hops are grown in the Alsace region of France.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Alsace is in, really, the, the, the border region between Germany and France.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
